Day_16 (Daily Problem)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Question
-------------
How Many Solutions Does This Quadratic Have?                              (11-08-2021)

A quadratic equation a x² + b x + c = 0 has either 0, 1, or 2 distinct solutions for real values of x. Given a, b and c, you should return the number of solutions to the equation.



Examples

solutions(1, 0, -1) ? 2

// x² - 1 = 0 has two solutions (x = 1 and x = -1).



solutions(1, 0, 0) ? 1

// x² = 0 has one solution (x = 0).



solutions(1, 0, 1) ? 0

// x² + 1 = 0 has no real solutions.

Notes

You do not have to calculate the solutions, just return how many there are.

a will always be non-zero.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:
----------
#include<iostream>

using namespace std;



int solutions(int ,int ,int);



int main(){

	cout<<solutions(1,0,1);

}

int solutions(int a,int b,int c){

	int disc;

	disc=b*b-4*a*c;

	if(disc>0){

		return 2;

	}

	else if(disc==0){

		return 1;

	}

	else if(disc<0){

		return 0;

	}

}
